# Solution Map: Smart Shopping List

## 1. Solution Intent

A smart shopping system that uses a 3-table pattern to control item behaviour via
configuration, validate inventory against an external system, and provide real-time
health feedback on the UI.

**Design principles:**
- Configuration over code: repeatable logic lives in config entities, not hardcoded
- Parity: every client-side rule has a server-side equivalent enforcing the same constraint
- External integrations wrapped in shared functions for reuse and testability

---

## 2. Platform Profile: Dataverse

This section maps every abstract component type to its concrete Dataverse implementation.
Agents reading this map should use Dataverse-native terminology when generating code,
but the architecture above this section is platform-agnostic.

| Abstract Type | Dataverse Concrete | Runtime | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|
| Data Entity | Dataverse Table (Entity) | Dataverse storage | Schema in `docs/dataverse-schema.md` |
| Server Logic | C# Plugin (.NET 4.6.2, sandbox) | Plugin Execution Pipeline | Registered via Plugin Registration Tool |
| Client Logic | TypeScript Form Script | Model-driven app form | Loaded as web resource, bound to form events |
| API | Custom API (contoso_ prefixed) | Dataverse Web API | Callable via `POST /api/data/v9.2/contoso_ApiName` |
| Shared Function | C# class/method in plugin assembly | Plugin Execution Pipeline | No independent deployment; linked at compile time |
| Background Process | Power Automate Flow | Power Automate runtime | Connector orchestration only; no business logic |
| UI Control | PCF Control (React + Fluent UI v9) | Model-driven app form | Bound to field or dataset |
| Config Pattern | contoso_Config* table + generic plugin handler | Plugin pipeline reads config at runtime | New rules = new rows, not code |
| Data Field | Dataverse Column (Attribute) | Dataverse storage | Only tracked here when it drives logic |
| Data Relationship | Dataverse Lookup / N:N | Dataverse storage | Cascade behaviour configured per relationship |
| Integration Boundary | External HTTP endpoint | Called from plugin via HttpClient | Sandboxed; outbound only |

---

## 3. Config Patterns

### FieldConcatenation
```yaml
kind: config-pattern
id: field-concatenation
lifecycle: active
```
- **intent:** Drives all field concatenation and formatting across all entities from config rows
- **config-entity:** [DE] contoso_configfieldrule
- **handler:** [SL] ConfigurableFieldConcatenator
- **applies-to:** [DE] contoso_shoppinglist
- **catalogue-ref:** docs/configuration-catalogue.md#contoso_ConfigFieldRule

### Validation
```yaml
kind: config-pattern
id: validation
lifecycle: active
```
- **intent:** Enforces validation rules (required, regex, range, cross-field) from config rows without hardcoding thresholds
- **config-entity:** [DE] contoso_configvalidation
- **handler:** [SL] ConfigurableValidator
- **applies-to:** [DE] contoso_listlineitem
- **catalogue-ref:** docs/configuration-catalogue.md#contoso_ConfigValidation

---

