## 11. Integration Boundaries [IB]

### [IB] ExternalInventoryAPI
```yaml
kind: integration-boundary
id: external-inventory-api
lifecycle: active
direction: outbound
owner: third-party (WarehouseCo)
```
- **intent:** External inventory management system — provides real-time stock availability data

**Contract:**
- Protocol: REST/HTTPS
- Auth: API key (header: `X-Api-Key`)
- Endpoint: `GET /api/v2/inventory/{itemId}/availability`
- Response: `{ "in_stock": bool, "available_qty": int, "last_updated": datetime }`
- SLA: 500ms p95 latency, 99.5% uptime

**Boundary:**
- Trust: external (crosses organisation boundary)
- Data classification: non-sensitive (stock levels only, no PII)
- Failure mode: [SL] ValidateItem throws user-facing error; [BP] VerifyStock retries 3x then dead-letters

**Operational:**
- Rate limit: 100 req/min per API key
- Circuit breaker: 5 consecutive failures > open for 30s
- Monitoring: Application Insights custom metric `inventory_api_latency_ms`

| depends_on | relationship | why |
|---|---|---|
| (external — not in solution) | — | Owned by WarehouseCo |

| depended_on_by | relationship | impact |
|---|---|---|
| [SF] InventoryApiClient.CheckStock | depends_on | All inventory calls route through this boundary |

---

## 12. Parity Contracts

Invariants that must hold across client and server. Every row is testable.

| Rule | Client Enforcement | Server Enforcement | Status |
|---|---|---|---|
| Quantity must not exceed item type max | [CL] EnforceQuantityLimit (warning on form) | [SL] ConfigurableValidator (blocks save) | ACTIVE |
| Nutrition score below threshold flags red | [CL] HighlightHealthStatus (visual indicator) | [SL] ValidateNutritionScore | **TODO — server side not built** |
| Out-of-stock items cannot be added | (no client-side check) | [SL] ValidateItem (blocks save) | PARTIAL — server only |

---

